{"name":"Blessing of the Sea","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/water/orb-ice-opaque.webp","system":{"description":"<p>You are blessed by the mighty Sea Fairy and therefore sea-related abilities have no effect on you. You receive 2 Additional Successes on each Defense Check you make to defend yourself against a Gift, spell, or action made using a Descriptor that includes the word 'sea'.</p>","notes":"This blessing protects against Enar's 'Rage of the Sea' Gift and any other sea-based threats. The Sea Fairy grants this after the Hunter demonstrates compassion for Enar rather than just wanting to kill him. The blessing is permanent for the Scenario but only affects sea-related powers.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"","source":"A Soldiers Duty","category":"scenario","scenario":"A Soldiers Duty","requirement":"Prove to the Sea Fairy your intention to do something for poor Enar.","scenarioSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","successes":0},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"source":"A Soldiers Duty","category":"scenario","scenario":"A Soldiers Duty","scenarioSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","sourceDirectory":"a-soldiers-duty","legacyId":"056390537e2d41fe","legacyType":"item","folderName":"A Soldiers Duty"}},"_id":"GS4swyBJ3C9IGVx5"}
{"name":"Art of Command","type":"gift","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","system":{"description":"<p>You've observed a good leader and figured out how to hone your strategies. Once per Scene, you can give an order to one of your allies and if they try to carry it out, they will receive 2 Additional Successes to any Check.</p>","notes":"This Gift is learned by observing Andersen's tactical command during battle. The Hunter must fight alongside Andersen during one of Enar's attacks (Day 1, 2, or 3) and survive the encounter. The order must be specific and tactical. This Gift is similar to Andersen's 'Commander' Gift but slightly less powerful (once per Scene vs. 3 times per Scene).","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"","source":"A Soldiers Duty","category":"scenario","scenario":"A Soldiers Duty","requirement":"Withstand an onslaught from Enar by fighting alongside Andersen.","scenarioSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","successes":0},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"source":"A Soldiers Duty","category":"scenario","scenario":"A Soldiers Duty","scenarioSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","sourceDirectory":"a-soldiers-duty","legacyId":"8733902a5d285313","legacyType":"item","folderName":"A Soldiers Duty"}},"_id":"2stgbbh1f7tlDLvP"}
{"name":"Coral of the Sea Fairy","type":"gift","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/pearl-pink.webp","system":{"description":"<p>You dispatched that hateful fairy and harnessed her soul in a lump of coral. Now her power is yours. You can use 1 Treasure Token to unlock this Gift for the duration of the Scenario. Spend 1 Soma to tap into the Coral's power and choose one of the following effects: **1. Water of Life:** A target recovers 1 Wound. **2. The Fury of the Sea:** The water of the sea engulfs everything, sweeping away all threats. Those who are within 30 feet must pass a Defense Check against OL Hard 7 to avoid being overwhelmed by the waves and being thrown away, suffering 1 Wound. **3. The Waves of the Sea:** You can travel to any point of the sea within 6 miles. This shift is instantaneous and you can take up to 2 subjects with you. **CURSE:** Sea creatures sense what you have done and will attack you without hesitation to try to free the soul of the Fairy.</p>","notes":"This is a DARK Gift only available to Marina the Sea Explorer if she murders the Sea Fairy. The Fairy refuses to help Marina initially due to her selfish reputation. If Marina kills her anyway, she can trap the Fairy's soul in coral and steal her powers. Requires spending 1 Treasure Token to unlock, then costs 1 Soma per use. The curse is permanent: all sea creatures (fish, whales, merfolk, sea monsters, etc.) become hostile and attack Marina on sight to free the trapped soul. This is a morally dark choice with serious consequences. The coral must be carried on Marina's person.","somaCost":1,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"","source":"A Soldiers Duty","category":"scenario","scenario":"A Soldiers Duty","requirement":"Kill the Sea Fairy. (Special gift for Marina the Sea Explorer only)","scenarioSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","successes":0},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"source":"A Soldiers Duty","category":"scenario","scenario":"A Soldiers Duty","scenarioSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","sourceDirectory":"a-soldiers-duty","legacyId":"935f46e4330faa68","legacyType":"item","folderName":"A Soldiers Duty"}},"_id":"b6bLQsLMq90gp4bG"}
{"name":"Marionettes' Destroyer","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/death/skull-horned-worn-fire-orange.webp","system":{"description":"<p>You know how to calm restless spirits by giving them a proper greeting when their soul is freed. You are not affected by the Boundless Rage Gift used by Marionettes. Additionally, you receive 1 Additional Success when defending against beings that are animated or controlled by spirits or magic (including possessed individuals, animated constructs, and undead thralls).</p>","notes":"The Marionettes are tortured souls bound by Azzurra into wooden bodies covered in flayed human flesh. They hate their existence and attack with Boundless Rage (final desperate OL 7 attack when defeated). This Gift allows the Hunter to free them peacefully and grants protection against necromantic animation and possession effects. Works against Azzurra's animated servants, possessed victims, and similar spirit-controlled entities.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"scenario","scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","requirement":"Defeat any Marionette OR understand that they are souls imprisoned against their will.","scenarioSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","successes":0},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"scenario","scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","scenarioSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","sourceDirectory":"of-flesh-and-wood","legacyId":"2be833a6ecd080ad","legacyType":"item","folderName":"Of Flesh and Wood"}},"_id":"kdBh9HbSnfFxo6WN"}
{"name":"A True Friend","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/life/heart-hand-glowing-white.webp","system":{"description":"<p>Carlo understands that he can trust you and will run to your aid if you need it. You can spend 1 Soma to have Carlo appear in the Scene as your NPC ally. Carlo will use the power of his lies (creating Descriptors that become temporarily real) to help you to the best of his ability. Carlo's presence lasts for the remainder of the Scene or until he suffers his 3rd Wound.</p>","notes":"Carlo is a living puppet animated by fairy magic whose lies become reality. His Gift 'Lies' allows him to create Descriptors centered on himself (examples: 'I can walk through walls', 'I am invisible to human eyes', 'I am strong as ten men'). Effects are literal and last 1 Scene. Gaining his trust requires: 1) Believing him over Azzurra, 2) Protecting him from Geppetto/Antonio, 3) Treating him as a person not an object. Once trusted, Carlo becomes a powerful ally who can reshape reality temporarily to aid the Hunter. This bond is permanent across scenarios—Carlo remembers his true friend.","somaCost":1,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"scenario","scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","requirement":"Gain Carlo's trust despite all his lies.","scenarioSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","successes":0},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"scenario","scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","scenarioSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","sourceDirectory":"of-flesh-and-wood","legacyId":"2ccded11cf980ebe","legacyType":"item","folderName":"Of Flesh and Wood"}},"_id":"LjXHeeYK89xUjQUa"}
{"name":"The Field of Miracles","type":"gift","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/terrain-hill-rocky.webp","system":{"description":"<p>You know Sinalunga well because it is where one of your secret shelters is located—the legendary Field of Miracles. Once per Scene you can spend 1 Soma so you or another subject can leave the Scene immediately and hide in the Field of Miracles. No one can find the exact location of the shelter while you are there. When you are at the Field, once per Session you can recover 1 Wound you have suffered through rest and recuperation.</p>","notes":"This is a special character-specific Scenario Gift only available to the pre-generated Hunter 'Cunning Machiavelli the Fox & Sly Bischeri the Cat'. The Field of Miracles is a reference to Pinocchio's story where the Fox and Cat trick Pinocchio. In this case, it's a legitimate secret hideout in Sinalunga that The Fox and the Cat use for their schemes. Mechanical benefits: 1) Emergency escape (1 Soma to leave Scene instantly with ally), 2) Perfect hiding place (unfindable), 3) Healing sanctuary (1 Wound/Session when resting there). This represents their extensive criminal network and safe houses across Europe.","somaCost":1,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"scenario","scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","requirement":"Arrive in Sinalunga. (SPECIAL GIFT - Only for The Fox and the Cat)","scenarioSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","successes":0},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"scenario","scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","scenarioSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","sourceDirectory":"of-flesh-and-wood","legacyId":"f7423639d218fa95","legacyType":"item","folderName":"Of Flesh and Wood"}},"_id":"C746LmJFCaDxFgAH"}
{"name":"Voice of the Spirits","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/perception/eye-ringed-glow-angry-small-teal.webp","system":{"description":"<p>With the right peace and focus, you can open your mind to the spirit world and communicate with restless souls. Spend 1 Soma to contact any creature with the Spirit Gift that you've previously encountered. You can communicate with the Spirit telepathically and understand what it says, even across distances. This communion lasts for the duration of a Scene or until you release it.</p>","notes":"This Gift allows communication with any spirit the Hunter has previously met, including Yvonne, the Restless Spirits in the catacombs, or any other creature with the Spirit Gift. It doesn't control spirits, only enables dialogue. Useful for: 1) Negotiating with Yvonne, 2) Learning information from Restless Spirits about her presence, 3) Understanding spirit motivations. The connection is empathic and telepathic—spirits can't lie through it but can refuse to answer.","somaCost":1,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"","source":"The Smile In the Darkness","category":"scenario","scenario":"The Smile In the Darkness","requirement":"You have been in contact with either the Spirit or Spiritualist Gifts (encountered Yvonne, Restless Spirits, or met Alizée).","scenarioSlug":"the-smile-in-the-darkness","successes":0},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"source":"The Smile In the Darkness","category":"scenario","scenario":"The Smile In the Darkness","scenarioSlug":"the-smile-in-the-darkness","sourceDirectory":"the-smile-in-the-darkness","legacyId":"33b2f3f74a135553","legacyType":"item","folderName":"The Smile In the Darkness"}},"_id":"wTOE46ZeU12rlyHb"}
{"name":"Exorcist","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/holy/prayer-hands-glowing-yellow.webp","system":{"description":"<p>You have learned how to use your skills against restless Spirits through sacred rites, prayers, blessed objects, or mystical practices. All your actions can now affect targets who have the Spirit Gift, bypassing their immunity to physical harm. Additionally, all Wounds you inflict on Spirits cannot be ignored or regenerated by the Spirit Gift—your attacks harm their spiritual essence permanently.</p>","notes":"This Gift makes the Hunter a true spirit hunter, capable of permanently harming entities like Yvonne and the Restless Spirits. Requirement details: 1) Must have appropriate Descriptor (priest, mage, witch hunter, occultist, etc.), 2) Must learn exorcism techniques from either Adrien (prayers, holy water, blessed weapons) or Alizée (spiritualist methods, binding rituals). Mechanical impact: Completely bypasses Spirit Gift's immunity and regeneration. The Hunter's sword, bullets, or bare hands can now wound spirit essence directly. Wounds dealt are permanent and don't heal when spirits dissipate. This is crucial for defeating Yvonne permanently—without this or magic, she regenerates endlessly.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"","source":"The Smile In the Darkness","category":"scenario","scenario":"The Smile In the Darkness","requirement":"Have a Church or Magic-related Descriptor AND talk to Father Adrien or Alizée about practices used against Spirits.","scenarioSlug":"the-smile-in-the-darkness","successes":0},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"source":"The Smile In the Darkness","category":"scenario","scenario":"The Smile In the Darkness","scenarioSlug":"the-smile-in-the-darkness","sourceDirectory":"the-smile-in-the-darkness","legacyId":"5d900e736e714329","legacyType":"item","folderName":"The Smile In the Darkness"}},"_id":"QCfRItTHZ94UF6eD"}
{"name":"Hugin and Munin","type":"gift","img":"icons/creatures/birds/corvid-raven-purple.webp","system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, you can ask for advice from Hugin and Munin, the ravens of Father Odin. Ask the Storyteller a question, choosing from among: **'Where should I go?'** **'How can I defeat that enemy?'** **'What is missing in my search?'** The Storyteller will answer with a cryptic sentence, which always includes a useful hint. Additionally, you get 1 Additional Success on all Defense Checks against an attack from a non-human creature, thanks to the blessing of Odin himself. **Cost:** At the beginning of each Scene, you must spend 1 Soma to feed the spirits of Hugin and Munin, or lose the use of this Gift for the rest of the Scenario.</p>","notes":"Hugin (Thought) and Munin (Memory) are Odin's ravens from Norse mythology. In Tuvstarr's Reflection, even the ancient gods want to stop the corruption spreading across the land. Random encounter 2 in the Wild Forest. The ravens approach and mentally communicate, offering their blessing. The cryptic answers guide without giving away solutions. The +1 success vs non-human creatures helps against Fairies, Hulder, Skutt, trolls, etc. Must pay 1 Soma at scene start to keep the gift active (feeding their spirits). Special rule: Unlike normal Scenario Gifts, this can be acquired WITHOUT an Interlude—immediately upon making the pact.","somaCost":1,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"","source":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","category":"scenario","scenario":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","requirement":"Meet Hugin and Munin in the Wild Forest and make a pact with them. (NO INTERLUDE REQUIRED in Sherazade stories)","scenarioSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","successes":0},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"source":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","category":"scenario","scenario":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","scenarioSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","sourceDirectory":"tuvstarrs-reflection","legacyId":"3d35aa895a3ee9ed","legacyType":"item","folderName":"Tuvstarrs Reflection"}},"_id":"Y0P3X9PBtRyhMw9V"}
{"name":"Lance of the Fallen Knight","type":"gift","img":"icons/weapons/polearms/spear-flared-purple.webp","system":{"description":"<p>When you wield this spear and obtain an Outcome with Increment on an attack, you can inflict 1 Additional Wound. The tip of the lance can ignite at will, casting light and allowing you to have a burning fire always near at hand. This enchanted ashwood spear with an iron point belonged to one of the brave knights who died searching for Princess Tuvstarr.</p>","notes":"Random encounter 3 in the Wild Forest. Black fumes fill the air, bubbles emerge from a dark pond. A knight in rusty armor lies dead, eyes white and puffy. The corpse holds this ashwood spear with iron point. Mechanical benefits: 1) +1 Wound on Increment attacks (powerful offensive boost). 2) Ignites at will for light and fire source (utility in dark forest). If the Hunters meet the Gallant Knight in the Dream World and possess this lance, he will ask them to return it to the castle in the real world as proof of his fallen brothers' sacrifice. The lance is a symbol of duty and sacrifice. Special rule: Can be acquired WITHOUT an Interlude—immediately upon taking it from the corpse.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"","source":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","category":"scenario","scenario":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","requirement":"Collect the lance from the dead knight's body found near a dark pond in the Wild Forest. (NO INTERLUDE REQUIRED in Sherazade stories)","scenarioSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","successes":0},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"source":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","category":"scenario","scenario":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","scenarioSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","sourceDirectory":"tuvstarrs-reflection","legacyId":"8092a773dfdcbbf6","legacyType":"item","folderName":"Tuvstarrs Reflection"}},"_id":"U158ohNYaxd6xFL6"}
